HEADWORD: Tsung tu
<hw>Tsung" tu`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A viceroy or
governor-general, the highest provincial official in China, with civil
and military authority over one or more provinces.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

